texts: All right, let's solve this thing and complete the quest!
I went back to last night, a little after Cicada 3301 posted.
What do you mean? You just said we're doing this.

texts: I already know everything about the quest. Listen up, it's—
For some reason, I was lying on the sofa.
One minute you were talking, the next you were on the floor. We carried you to the sofa...
You can't just put all your energy into showing off to your gf! Gotta save some for self-care.
The last time here, I'd spent hours solving the puzzle and I was doing pretty good.
Why had I passed out? And did I just see...?
You don't look so good. Are you okay?
Wait, this was no time to rest!
Lemme tell you about the quest.
I told them the details of the Hihack, and asked them to help me stop it from happening.
In this state though, I couldn't get them to believe a word I said. Not that I blamed them.
All I did was invite more worrying about my well-being.
I tried to do something about it myself...
...But /hack/ treated everything I said as disinfo, and my warnings to Thousand Air were ignored.
I even tried sending a bomb threat to JA1037E, but after the airline looked into it, they decided it wasn't worth acting on.
You really think you can prevent a quest before it happens? I mean, we don't even know if it's actually gonna happen in the first place.
It will! Just think about this seriously, would ya!

texts: I forced Cross and Wind to help me out, and tried some more ideas with them...
Still, I couldn't give up just yet...
You woke up! What a relief!
I shook off my drowsiness and slowly got up.
Everyone was looking at me with worry in their eyes, but I had to ignore their concern. I rushed to gather info through my BMI.
If I didn't do anything about JA1037E before it took off, I'd be back at square one. There'd be no point in having Loaded at all.
I had to do something decisive to stop the quest from happening.
And I had to do it while I was still conscious!
But how?! What was the best way to stop it?!
As I scanned through the reams of text, something caught my eye.
I'd already shaken up the internet with my bomb threat, so...
Yeah. I should blow it up.
Cicada won't be able to set up his quest if there's no 037E.
But that's a crime! That's not like you—
I don't care! It's gonna save hundreds of lives!
I wouldn't let anyone stop me.
I hacked into the Ninoy Aquino International Airport.
After I'd sent the bomb threat, JA1037E was sent to a hangar for inspection.
I didn't see anyone nearby or on the plane itself.
I hacked a nearby refueling truck and had it gradually leak jet fuel.
I directed it towards the plane, then set the hangar's maintenance equipment to full capacity, so they'd heat up.
Jet fuel. Heat. JA1037E. The moment they met...

texts: I stopped the quest before it even happened!
The scenery was so unfamiliar I couldn't even tell whether this was reality or a dream.
A sudden headache made me groan in pain.
That's no surprise. You passed out and hit your head.
I must've lost consciousness right after JA1037E exploded.
Momo was sleeping in a nearby chair. Had she been by my side this whole time?
Life sure wasn't easy when you just randomly fainted over and over.
What was that about, anyway? A side-effect of the Loading?
I'd prevented the incident, but now I was...
Cicada made another post about four hours ago. The text we got from it was UA6271B.
Cicada changed his target. The quest isn't over.
All that work was for nothing?!
Wait, I can just blow it up again...!
No, you can't! It's already taken off from the airport!

texts: I rushed to check the quest status.
I saw Momo at the edge of my vision. She was looking at me with tears in her eyes.
A chill ran down my spine.
No one could prevent the incident.
I couldn't even figure out a way to stop it this time.
Flight 114, carrying over 200 passengers, fell from the sky and crashed in Odaiba.
